  <h2>Key Terms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>CAUTI:</strong> Catheter-associated urinary tract infection — most common HAI; prevented by aseptic technique and early removal.</li>
    <li><strong>Peristalsis:</strong> Wave-like muscle contractions that move contents through the GI tract.</li>
    <li><strong>Stoma:</strong> Surgically created opening in the abdominal wall for waste elimination.</li>
    <li><strong>Colostomy:</strong> Stoma formed from the colon.</li>
    <li><strong>Ileostomy:</strong> Stoma formed from the ileum; produces liquid output.</li>
    <li><strong>Fecal impaction:</strong> Accumulation of hardened stool that cannot be passed voluntarily.</li>
  </ul>
